      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "title: \"Fasting, Body Composition, and Lifestyle Patterns by Age Group\"\n",
        "format: html\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Analysis Objective\n",
        "\n",
        "This report explores how fasting measurements, BMI, body size, sex, and lifestyle-related variables vary across two age groups:\n",
        "\n",
        "- `Age <= 30`\n",
        "- `Age > 30`\n",
        "\n",
        "The objective is to identify descriptive patterns, compare distributions, and examine how anthropometric and metabolic variables behave across these two age-based segments.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Import necessary libraries"
      ],
      "id": "8507419a"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "from dotenv import load_dotenv"
      ],
      "id": "92699dff",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Set the visual theme"
      ],
      "id": "1f2f5308"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sns.set_theme(\n",
        "    style=\"whitegrid\",\n",
        "    context=\"notebook\",\n",
        "    rc={\"figure.figsize\": (8, 5)}\n",
        ")"
      ],
      "id": "6f5f2de1",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Load the dataset"
      ],
      "id": "6613ffb1"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "load_dotenv()\n",
        "\n",
        "dataset_path = os.getenv(\"CLEANED_DATASET_PATH\")\n",
        "if dataset_path is None:\n",
        "    raise ValueError(\"CLEANED_DATASET_PATH is not set in the environment.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "df = pd.read_excel(dataset_path)\n",
        "df.head()"
